-------------------------------
Affixes: Esperanto roots are used since English words tend to form bulky consonent clusters
(lenplasu -> leneyu)
Also, it will bring a good habit of word-building from Esperanto

na-: mal- ; un-
re-: re- ; re-
ek- ; ek- ; x
eks- ; eks- ; x
mis- ; mis- ; mis-
-ad ; -ad ; -ment, -ing (-ing is too polysemic)
-as ; -aĵ ; -thing
-an ; -an -er ; -member -part
-up ; -ar ; -group -ry (-ar too similar to -er)
-abl ; -ebl ; -abl
-es ; -ec ; -ness -ship
-od ; x ; -ish -oid
-eg ; -eg ; x
-or ; x (pli) ; -er (to not confuse it with the french -eur/-er)
-ost ; x (plej) ; -est
-et ; -et ; many
-em ; -em ; tendency to 
-end ; -end ; x
-ind ; -ind ; x
-ey ; -ej -uj -ing ; -place
-er ; -ulo -anto -isto (profesiulo) ?-il ; -er (intence malpreciza)
-bos (-estr ne estas tre ofta)
? -ig ; -ig ; x (really risky as people may use it to verbs (they are already transitive)
? -iĝ ; -iĝ ; x (really really risky, people should use -e) 
? -il ; -il ; -tool (teorie -er sufiĉas, kaj la rezulto per -er pli rekoneblas, sed eble utilas por krei distingojn ! sed tiam ni povas uzi -tul) 
-ism ; mapped on English (careful, isma is about a school of thoughts)
-ist ; mapped on English (careful, ista is about a person that follows a school of thoughts) (atentu Esperantistoj, ne temas pri profesio)
-os ; -plena ; -ful
-obl
-on
-op
-um (use it to create words in the go, please do not standardize words with it such as "brakumo" or "operaciumo" because they are lazy and imprecise)
